Project wiring of CLAUDE.md '@AGENTS.md' + .gm/next-step.md seeding (ensureNextStepWiring) MUST live in gm-plugkit/bootstrap.js ensureReady() — the watcher boot path that runs in EVERY consumer project (bun x gm-plugkit spool) — not only in repo-root bin/bootstrap.js + lib/skill-bootstrap.js, which never execute when a foreign project (e.g. C:/dev/tv8) boots its own watcher. SYMPTOM that exposed the gap (2026-06-11): tv8 had AGENTS.md + a live watcher + .gm/next-step.md (rewritten by the running orchestrator) but NO CLAUDE.md, so Claude Code never auto-included AGENTS.md. FIX: added ensureNextStepWiring(CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR||cwd) call unconditionally at top of ensureReady (before the isReady early-return, else warm-boot skips it). gm-plugkit/package.json version is auto-bumped + republished by publish.yml on any non-ignored push to gm main, so JS-only gm-plugkit fixes ship without a wasm/plugkitVersion cascade."